                   <p>
                    <strong>
                     <span style="font-size: 16px;">
                      NORTHERN TRANSITIONS TO HOLD FINAL HOUSEHOLD HAZARDOUS WASTE COLLECTION
                     </span>
                    </strong>
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                     Northern Transitions in the Soo is holding their final waste collection for the summer on Saturday, July 28, 2018.  Mackinac County residents may bring items there.  There is a charge per pound and you
                     <span style="text-decoration: underline;">
                      must
                     </span>
                     call to make an appointment.  It starts at 9 AM.
                    </span>
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                     Household waste:  $1.10 per pound
                     <br/>
                    </span>
                    <span style="font-size: small;">
                     CRT TV and monitors:  $.40 per pound
                     <br/>
                    </span>
                    <span style="font-size: small;">
                     Electronics:  $.25 per pound
                     <br/>
                    </span>
                    <span style="font-size: small;">
                     Examples of things they will take: Oil based paints and stains, motor oil, pesticides, cleaners, fluorescent bulbs, dry cell batteries.
                    </span>
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    <strong>
                     CALL: 906-635-5681 and dial "0" for operator!
                    </strong>
                   </p>
                  </div>

             <div class="DnnModule DnnModule-DNN_HTML DnnModule-5980">
              <a name="5980">
              </a>
              <div class="Container-20015-4">
               <div class="contentmain1">
                <div class="dnntitle">
                 <span class="title4" id="dnn_ctr5980_dnnTITLE4_titleLabel">
                 </span>
                </div>
                <div class="contentpane" id="dnn_ctr5980_ContentPane">
                 <!-- Start_Module_5980 -->
                 <div class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC" id="dnn_ctr5980_ModuleContent">
                  <div class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr5980_HtmlModule_lblContent">
                   <strong>
                    <em>
                    </em>
                   </strong>
                   <div style="font-size: small;">
                   </div>
                   <div style="font-style: italic; font-size: small;">
                   </div>
                   <p style="text-align: center;">
                    <span style="font-size: 16px; color: #c00000;">
                     <strong>
                     </strong>
                    </span>
                   </p>
                   <strong>
                   </strong>
                   <p style="text-align: center;">
                    <span style="font-size: 16px; color: #c00000;">
                     <strong>
                      The Clark Township Board of Trustees meet on the
                     </strong>
                    </span>
                   </p>
                   <p style="text-align: center;">
                    <strong style="color: #c00000; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
                     3rd Wednesday of every month at 8:00 AM at the Township Offices on North Blind Line Road.
                    </strong>
                   </p>
                   <p style="text-align: center;">
                   </p>
                   <p style="text-align: center;">
                    <strong style="color: #c00000; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
                    </strong>
                   </p>
                   <hr/>
                   <strong style="color: #c00000; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
                   </strong>
                   <p style="font-style: italic; font-size: small; text-align: center;">
                   </p>
                   <div style="text-align: justify;">
                    <span style="text-align: left;">
                     Located in Michigan's Eastern Upper Peninsula, Clark Township comprises the two waterfront settlements of Cedarville and Hessel,
                    </span>
                    a 17 mile stretch of pristine shoreline and the 36-island archipelago known as the Les Cheneaux Islands.
                   </div>
                   <div style="text-align: justify;">
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                   <em>
                    <div style="font-size: small; text-align: justify;">
                     <em>
                      The northern shore of Lake Huron, including Clark Township, has been referred to as "One of the Last Great Places" in the northern hemisphere.
                     </em>
                    </div>
                    <div style="text-align: justify;">
                     <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                      <br/>
                     </span>
                    </div>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                     <div style="text-align: justify;">
                      <em style="font-size: 12px;">
                       <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                        Many of the people who call this place home trace their lineage back to the original founding families of the early 1800's; others have come here more recently to visit and decided to stay. We are also blessed with a large multi-generational seasonal population, whose families have helped to shape the history and development of Clark Township.
                       </span>
                      </em>
                     </div>
                    </span>
                    <div style="text-align: justify;">
                     <br/>
                    </div>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                     <div style="text-align: justify;">
                      <em style="font-size: 12px;">
                       <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                        Together, we are a community with much in common - we love the outdoors and our natural surroundings. We enjoy boating, hunting and fishing, walking and bicycling, gardening, cross-country skiing and snowmobiling. We treasure our artisans and creative people, our library, schools and cultural events. We have an abundance of service organizations and a tremendous spirit of volunteerism.
                       </span>
                      </em>
                     </div>
                    </span>
                    <div style="text-align: justify;">
                     <br/>
                    </div>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                     <div style="text-align: justify;">
                      <em style="font-size: 12px;">
                       <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                        The Les Cheneaux Islands Area has a traditional economy of tourism and related service businesses, a heritage of wooden boats and boatbuilding, and a multitude of artisans and craft workers. We are interested in diversification and welcome new additions to our business sectors.
                       </span>
                      </em>
                     </div>
                    </span>
                    <div style="text-align: justify;">
                     <br/>
                    </div>
                    <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                     <div style="text-align: justify;">
                      <em style="font-size: 12px;">
                       <span style="font-size: 13px;">
                        Come join us!
                       </span>
                      </em>
                     </div>
                    </span>
                   </em>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <!-- End_Module_5980 -->
                </div>
                <div class="c_footer_1">
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="DnnModule DnnModule-DNN_HTML DnnModule-12363">

              </a>
              <div class="Container-20015-4">

              </a>
              <div class="Container-20015-4">
               <div class="contentmain1">
                <div class="dnntitle">
                 <span class="title4" id="dnn_ctr12230_dnnTITLE4_titleLabel">
                 </span>
                </div>
                <div class="contentpane" id="dnn_ctr12230_ContentPane">
                 <!-- Start_Module_12230 -->
                 <div class="DNNModuleContent ModDNNHTMLC" id="dnn_ctr12230_ModuleContent">
                  <div class="Normal" id="dnn_ctr12230_HtmlModule_lblContent">
                   <p>
                    <span style="font-size: 16px; color: #0070c0;">
                     <strong>
                      PROGRAM FOR SENIORS AT CLARK TOWNSHIP COMMUNITY CENTER
                     </strong>
                    </span>
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    Clark Township and the CLM Community Action Agency have an established satellite office at the Clark Township Community Center to serve local residents.  Sherrie Pitko is the the Mackinac and Chippewa County outreach worker, Senior Services Director. She is available Monday thru Thursday from 9:00 AM to 3:00 PM.  Please call (906)440-6712 or 484-1069 to schedule an appointment.
                   </p>
                   <p>
                    The Township and CLM Community Action also host Senior Meals at the Community Center On Monday, Wednesday and Friday.  There are
                    <strong>
                     no income restrictions.
                    </strong>
                    Anyone over the age of 60 is welcome.  Call 484-1061 by 8:30 AM to reserve your spot!  Meals are a $2.50 donation to seniors and $5.00 for guests.  If you feel you qualify for "Meals-on-Wheels", please contact Sherrie Pitko for assistance in completing the required forms. She will also be able to tell you the requirements for this program.
                   </p>
                  </div>
                 </div>
                 <!-- End_Module_12230 -->
                </div>
                <div class="c_footer_1">
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
